
asadmin Utility Subcommands                  verify-domain-xml(1)

NAME
     verify-domain-xml - verifies the content of  the  domain.xml
     file

SYNOPSIS
     verify-domain-xml [--help]
      [ --domaindir  domain-dir] [domain-name]

DESCRIPTION
     Verifies the content of the domain.xml file. This subcommand
     is supported in local mode only.

OPTIONS
     -h --help

         Displays the help text for the subcommand.

     --domaindir
         Specifies the directory where the domains  are  located.
         The  path  must  be  accessible  in the file system. The
         default  is  the  value  of   the   $AS_DEF_DOMAINS_PATH
         environment  variable.  This  variable is defined in the
         file asenv.bat or asenv.conf. The default value of  this
         variable is as-install/domains.

OPERANDS
     domain_name

         Specifies  the  name  of  the  domain.  The  default  is
         domain1.

EXAMPLES
     Example 1 Using verify-domain-xml

       asadmin> verify-domain-xml --verbose=true
       All Tests Passed.
       domain.xml is valid

EXIT STATUS
     0                   command executed successfully

     1                   error in executing the command

